node.text:
Do what you love. Don't listen to anyone else who tells you not to do it. You do what you want, what you love.
-
Couldn’t have imagined I’d be where I was today a decade ago. If I were to have listen to everyone else I would of never taken the leap of faith.
-
Find your passion and dedicate all your attention, focus, and energy to that one thing!
-
My last only Olympia routine. Love watching this video cause it makes me fired up to get back up there!!

node.text:
Nothing great in the world has ever been accomplished without passion.
-
When you identify your passion and align it with whatever you’re doing, a magical synergy happens that will effortlessly carry you to new heights. Work becomes enjoyable. Hours fly by. Soreness and fatigue take a backseat as you power your way to greater achievements.
-
Work extremely hard and love what you do. Yes. There’s always going to be someone more talented than you, but there's no substitute for passion. People who are passionate always work the hardest, and that sets them apart!
-
#repost @makaveli_motivation

node.text:
It isn’t something that is handed to you, you must earn that feeling.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Weight lifting is ultimately what created that feeling for me. The state of constantly working on my body, learning about training, and staying on top of my eating and sleep habits gave me gratification that I was accomplishing something every single day. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
By being in a state of growth on a consistent basis, it translated to my work, relationships, and overall well-being. Ultimately, that shaped the opportunities to do what I love every single day. And that’s the feeling I would like to create for each and every one of you out there. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣

node.text:
Every outstanding athlete has encountered injuries or physical limitations, every successful business has at one point lost money, and every great student has failed a test.⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
However, every failure should be viewed optimistically. It is now a chance to improve your knowledge gaps to continue to move forward in the future, and is now a problem that you have a better idea of how to solve the next time. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
How you deal with failures or adversity will determine the quality of how you will live the rest of your life, so don’t hold yourself back by being consumed by negative energy. The faster you’re able to flip to a positive mindset, the faster you’ll be able to accomplish the task ahead of you. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
✖️Slots now available for @beyondthephysique transformation challenge now!

node.text:
🚨ALL ABOUT LEG DAY
If you’re looking to build legendary legs, you need absolute control of how you stimulate them. You need to address your strengths and weaknesses strategically. The anatomy of the quad is essentially the same as the arm, so it can be helpful to think about the way you train arms when you approach your leg training.

Think of your Quads as the triceps of your legs. They serve to extend the leg using 4 smaller muscles that originate around the hip and connect to the knee.

💥4 Muscles in the Quads
1️⃣Vastus lateralis
2️⃣Vastus medialus
3️⃣Vastus intermedius
4️⃣Rectus femoris

The Hamstrings are the biceps of the legs. They serve the very important role of stabilizing the squat and helping to hinge the hips. The hamstrings can make or break your leg routine and therefore it is important to learn a bit about them and make sure that you take care of them. It’s very common for people to have very shortened, tight hamstrings. This can lead to postural problems and can only compromise your squat and deadlift form, but it can make performing normal life activities like tying your shoes hard.

node.text:
🚨Please Read Below

So many people jump from program to program and never see results. That’s mostly because those people aren’t understanding why one set of workouts “works” for them but the other may not. If you aren’t isolating variables and seeing how they work one at a time, you won’t be able to tell which is the variable that is working for your and which might be hindering your progress. You’re going to have to come up with your own process.

🚨Buy 1 Get 1 Free Coaching Plans
Get 2x The Time Being Coached For The Price Of 1

⏲Ends In 3 Days - Link In My Bio

🌐COACHINGWITHSADIK.COM (LINK IN BIO)

Let’s talk about some of the most important training variables that you should play with to individualize your training. Always to start with the most basic program and slowly add or subtract one thing at a time. It’s probably a good idea to write things down too. Keep a journal if that’s your style, or just take notes in your phone.

I will say that more is NOT always better. So if you think starting with a 5x5 program with two isolation movements per day is very basic and you’re not getting the results you want, so you increase your training volume, frequency, and load all at the same time, you may actually regress due to overreaching for too long and not managing your fatigue properly or increasing your food intake appropriately.

It’s not about simply doing more all the time. It’s just about striking the right balance and finding the upper limits of your training capacity.
